China Guangdong Plans Bid for U.K.’s Kalahari Minerals, Sunday Times Says

-- B y   M a r i a   E r m a k o v a
-- 
2011-10-09T07:42:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-09/china-guangdong-plans-bid-for-u-k-s-kalahari-sunday-times-says.html
China Guangdong Nuclear Power Group
Co. is preparing a 650 million-pound bid for  Kalahari Minerals
Plc (KAH) , a U.K.-based uranium miner,  the Sunday Times  reported,
without saying where they obtained the information..  China Guangdong has reopened talks with Kalahari over a 270
pence-a-share bid after withdrawing an offer of 290 pence-a-
share made in March because of the crisis at  Japan ’s Fukushima
nuclear plant, according to the newspaper.  The Chinese company is being advised by  Deutsche Bank AG (DBK) ,
while Kalahari has hired Ambrian Partners Ltd., the Sunday Times
said. An agreed transaction could be announced as soon as this
week, according to the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Maria Ermakova in  London  at 
 mermakova@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
